result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:23 AM 
Defendant Ashley M. Barrientes-Womack in court, in custody.
Attorney Francesco J Balistrieri in court for Ashley M. Barrientes-Womack.
Attorney Brendaliz Valdes in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Court Reporter:  Jan Leibhan.  Clerk:  JM.
MINUTES:
22CF1085:
Victim rights compliance.
Defendant entered a plea of No Contest to Ct 1-Fel. Take & Drive Veh. w/o Consent, Repeater dropped;
Found guilty by the court; Cts 2, 3, 4 were dismissed and read-in on State's motion. 
Federal firearms warning and voter ineligibility status given to the defendant. 
Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay the surcharge, notice given to def. in court. 
Presentence Investigation ordered.
Bond motion heard; Court grants bond motion so def. can enroll in the Vivitrol Program.
Court amends the cash bond to a $500 sign bond w/same conds, effective on 11/1/2022.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 6, 2023 at 10:30 am.

Case dismissed and read-in with 22CF1085 on State's motion.

Case dismissed and read-in with 22CF1085 on State's motion.

Defense counsel requests an adjournment; needs add'l time for discovery/negotiations.  No objection by the State.  JPTC adj to 10/31/22 @ 11:15am.
No disposition. Leave on for next scheduled court activity.
